description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for an enthusiastic experienced clinical psychologist to join our dynamic, well established psychological services team within the Ealing community team for people with learning disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers excellent opportunities for joint working alongside a range of professionals (speech and language therapy, music and art therapy, psychiatry, nursing, social work and physiotherapy) to deliver holistic support to people with learning disabilities, their families and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders responsibilities will include delivering specialist psychological assessment and intervention, both to individuals, families and groups; contributing to staff training and providing psychological advice and consultation to professional and non-professional carers. The post holder will also provide supervision to both qualified and assistant psychologists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would be keen to receive applications from qualified clinical psychologists with significant experience of working with people with learning disabilities and their families.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be registered with the HCPC on appointment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a temporary contract for 1 year covering maternity leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brian Leaning. Head of Psychology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: brianleaning@nhs.net Tel: 07725849173&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
